On the basis of study regulations, student's guide and other relevant materials the student will acquire basic knowledge about the organisation of studies at the law school. The student will become familiar with possibilities to design one's own studies and opportunities of non-classroom activities for law students. The course will provide an ovrview of different learning styles and study skills.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to help students to aquire knowledge and skills needed at the university.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student
-	knows the study regulations of Tartu University and its specifics at the law school;
-	knows the students' rights and duties;
-	 plans one's studies at the law school in a conscious and practical manner;
-	has knowledge about one's own peculiarities as a learner;
-	knows the structure of the Tartu University Law School.
